\
\cb3 Regulatory and Algorithmic Updates: Social media platforms frequently update their features and algorithms (like how longer videos might become more favorable, or new features like YouTube Shorts adding clickable links, etc.). The app should have a mechanism to update its best practices and AI parameters accordingly. For example, if Instagram suddenly prioritizes Reels with original audio over those with music, the app should adapt its recommendations. This vertical improvement means having a team or process to keep the AI\'92s knowledge current with platform changes (possibly through machine learning updates or manual rule tweaks informed by industry news). Essentially, the app\'92s intelligence should evolve in tandem with the platforms it targets, always giving users an edge.\cb1 \
